SIMPLE: umpire
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Umpire
<hw>Um"pire</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>nompere</ets>, <ets>nounpere</ets> (also <ets>impier</ets>, fr. F.
<ets>impair</ets> uneven), fr. OF. <ets>nomper</ets> uneven, F.
<ets>non-pair</ets>; hence the meaning, uneven, <it>i. e.</it>, third
person; <ets>non</ets> not + OF. <ets>per</ets> even, equal, peer, F.
<ets>pair</ets>; cf. L. <ets>impar</ets> uneven, unequal. See
<er>Non-</er>, and <er>Peer</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A person to whose sole decision a controversy or
question between parties is referred; especially, one chosen to see that
the rules of a game, as cricket, baseball, or the like, are strictly
observed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A man, in questions of this kind, is able to be a skillful
<qex>umpire</qex> between himself and others.</q>
<rj><qau>Barrow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A third person, who is to decide a
controversy or question submitted to arbitrators in case of their
disagreement.</def> <rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Judge; arbitrator; referee. See
<er>Judge</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Umpire</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Umpire
<hw>Um"pire</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Umpired</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Umpiring</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To decide as umpire;
to arbitrate; to settle, as a dispute.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Judges appointed to <qex>umpire</qex> the matter in contest
between them, and to decide where the right lies.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To perform the duties of umpire in or for; <as>as,
to <ex>umpire</ex> a game</as>.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Umpire</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Umpire
<hw>Um"pire</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To act as umpire or
arbitrator.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Umpireship</ent>⟦br⟧
